# Manual HTTP probes for the membership module (Phase 2 / Slice 5).
#
# How to use:
#   1. Start the server with `task run`.
#   2. Open this file in JetBrains GoLand/IntelliJ or in VSCode with the
#      REST Client extension installed.
#   3. Click the gutter icon next to a request to send it.
#
# Substitute <memberId> after the first POST returns.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### POST {{baseUrl}}/members — register a member
POST {{baseUrl}}/members
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ada Lovelace",
  "email": "ada.lovelace@example.com"
}

### GET {{baseUrl}}/members/<memberId> — find a member by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/members/<memberId>

### PATCH {{baseUrl}}/members/<memberId>/suspend — flip status to SUSPENDED
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/members/<memberId>/suspend

### PATCH {{baseUrl}}/members/<memberId>/reactivate — flip status back to ACTIVE
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/members/<memberId>/reactivate

### PATCH {{baseUrl}}/members/<memberId>/tier — upgrade membership tier
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/members/<memberId>/tier
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tier": "PREMIUM"
}

### GET {{baseUrl}}/members/<memberId>/eligibility — check eligibility
GET {{baseUrl}}/members/<memberId>/eligibility
